{"title_page": "Escape from Tarkov", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|{{Tone|date=September 2019}}{{Lead too short|date=January 2020}}{{3p|date=March 2020}}}}\n{{Infobox video game\n| title = Escape from Tarkov\n| image = Escape from Tarkov.jpg\n| caption = Cover art for ''Escape from Tarkov''\n| developer = Battlestate Games\n| publisher = Battlestate Games\n| engine = [[Unity (game engine)|Unity]]\n| platforms = [[Microsoft Windows]]\n| genre = [[Action RPG]], [[Simulator]], [[First-person shooter]]\n| modes = [[Multi-player video game|Multi-player]], [[Arena-mode]], [[Nonlinear gameplay|Freeroam]]\n| released = Unreleased (Closed beta released on July 27th, 2017)\n| designer = \n| writer = \n| composer = \n| alt = \n}}\n\n'''''Escape from Tarkov''''' is an [[Indie game|indie]], [[Massively multiplayer online game|massively multiplayer online]] (MMO), [[first-person shooter]] (FPS) [[video game]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.escapefromtarkov.com/#about|title=About|website=www.escapesfromtarkov.com|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref> being developed by the Russian studio Battlestate Games to be released on [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]]. It is set in the fictional Norvinsk region in [[Northwest Russia|Northwestern Russia]], where a war is taking place between two [[Private military company|private military companies]] (United Security and BEAR) over a [[political scandal]] regarding the area's \"[[special economic zone]]\". The player is tasked with escaping the city of Tarkov by either joining one of the private military companies, or by trying to acquire precious loot from the sealed areas.\n\nA closed [[Video game development#Alpha|alpha]] of the game was first made available to select users on August 4, 2016,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.escapefromtarkov.com/news/id/28|title=Closed Alpha testing announce|website=www.escapesfromtarkov.com|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref> followed by a closed beta in July 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.escapefromtarkov.com/news/id/68|title=Closed Beta will start in July!|website=www.escapesfromtarkov.com|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref>\n\n== Gameplay ==\nThe developers of ''Escape from Tarkov'' refer the game as a realistic and hardcore [[first-person shooter]] [[Role-playing video game|role-playing]] video game that borrows elements from [[Massively multiplayer online game|massively multiplayer online games]].<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/escape-from-tarkov-pre-orders-all-early-access-edi/1100-6472569/|title=Escape From Tarkov Pre-Orders: All Early Access Editions Compared|website=GameSpot|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref><ref name=\":5\" /> In its current state, ''Escape from Tarkov'' incorporates several modes for the players to play: online [[Private military company|PMC]] raids, scav raids (short for \"scavenger\"),<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamespot.com/videos/what-is-the-new-scav-faction-in-escape-from-tarkov/2300-6437413/|title=What Is The New Scav Faction In Escape From Tarkov?|website=GameSpot|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pcgamesn.com/escape-from-tarkov/how-to-guide-tips|title=How to escape from Tarkov: our tips and guide|website=PCGamesN|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref><ref name=\":6\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/2020/1/21/21071120/escape-from-tarkov-guide-how-to-best-loot-scav-run-explained|title=Escape from Tarkov guide: How to get the best loot from a Scav run|last=Goslin|first=Austen|date=2020-01-21|website=Polygon|language=en|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref> and a temporary offline mode.<ref name=\":2\" /> In these raids, players can choose to play solo or go in groups and spawn on one side of a variety of maps to choose from in the game.<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.pcgamer.com/escape-from-tarkov-is-a-daunting-and-savage-evolution-of-battle-royale/|title=Escape From Tarkov is a daunting and savage evolution of battle royale|last=Messner|first=Steven|date=2020-01-18|website=PC Gamer|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref> Once spawned in, the players are given an extraction point on the other side of the map, and must fight against other players and scav [[Non-player character|non-player characters]] (NPC) to reach that point in order to escape.<ref name=\":4\" /> In addition to combat, players can also find loot in these maps such as firearms, equipment, armor, etc. and once extracted, can store their loot in a stash to use in future raids or can be sold in a flea market.<ref name=\":4\" />\n\nWhen players die in a raid, they lose everything, including loot and the equipment they brought into the raid.<ref name=\":4\" /> Players can insure weapons and equipment they brought in to increase the chances of retaining it if the gear is not taken by other players.<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.pcgamesn.com/escape-from-tarkov/how-to-guide-tips|title=How to escape from Tarkov: our tips and guide|website=PCGamesN|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref><ref name=\":4\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/pc-exclusive-shooter-escape-from-tarkov-closed-bet/1100-6451230/|title=PC-Exclusive Shooter Escape From Tarkov Closed Beta Date Announced|website=GameSpot|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref> As mentioned before, players can also play as a scav in a raid, where players are given a random loadout to use and do not lose anything from their stash when they die as a scav, making scav modes a learning source in the game.<ref name=\":3\" /><ref name=\":4\" /> If a player dies as a scav, there is a cooldown timer until the scav mode becomes available again for the player.<ref name=\":6\" />\n\nWhile not in a raid, players can sell their loot to traders that are provided by the game. These traders can provide a variety of quests that players can fulfill to increase their trader loyalty to get access to more items that can be purchased from the trader and more quests as well.<ref name=\":5\" /> Players can also settle and upgrade a living area called \"the Hideout,\" which is an underground bomb shelter that once upgraded with the materials needed, give the players in-game bonuses.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamepur.com/guides/escape-from-tarkov-hideout|title=What does the Escape from Tarkov Hideout do?|date=2020-01-17|website=Gamepur|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref> These bonuses include reducing the cooldown timer to play as a scav.<ref name=\":6\" />\n\n=== Combat ===\n{{Expand section|date=March 2020}}\n''Escape from Tarkov'' has combat that could be described as hardcore and realistic. The player has potential access to a variety of weapons ranging from AR's, SMG's, shotguns, sniper rifles, etc. All of these weapons, adjacent to other shooter games, are effective at various ranges dependent upon several variables like player position and distance from the enemy. Weapon effectiveness and functionality is heavily dependent upon the attachments and mods that the player installs on the weapon, such as sights and barrel attachments. The major difference between the combat in ''Escape from Tarkov'' and other FPS games is how damage is dealt. Instead of a standard health bar, players take damage to different areas and limbs of the body. Depending on the weapon type and the damage dealt, various status effects can be applied to a player's limbs that drastically effect how the PC moves and functions such as fractures and bleeding. Damage can be effectively avoided depending on player movement and gear. Body armor can protect certain areas of the body and leaning mechanics can allow a player to reduce their visible hit box to the enemy.\nObservers find ''Escape from Tarkov''<nowiki/>'s hardcore combat to be similar to that of [[Bohemia Interactive|Bohemia Interactive's]] [[ARMA (series)|''ARMA'']].<ref name=\":4\" />\n\n== Synopsis ==\n\n=== Setting ===\n''Escape from Tarkov'' is set in the fictional city of Tarkov, the capital of the Norvinsk [[Special economic zone|Special Economic Zone]] in [[Northwest Russia|Northwestern Russia]] between the year 2015 and 2026.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://unity.com/madewith/escape-from-tarkov|title=Escape from Tarkov by Battlestate Games - A shooter {{!}} Made with Unity|last=|first=|date=|website=Unity Technologies|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref> Political scandals and collapse of corruptions have resulted in the social breakdown of Tarkov and warring factions have turned the city into a shell of itself with sections of the city being under control of aggressive locals called \"scavs.\"<ref name=\":0\" /> As of March 2020, players can play across seven of the game's playable locations all within Tarkov: Factory, Customs, Woods, Shoreline, Interchange, The Lab, and Reserve.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dexerto.com/escape-from-tarkov/all-escape-from-tarkov-maps-and-extraction-points-guide-1309294|title=All Escape from Tarkov maps and extraction points guide|website=Dexerto.com|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref> Streets of Tarkov as of March 2020 is a location under development and is planned to become the next playable location in the game.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.futuregamereleases.com/2020/01/battlestate-games-shares-eft-streets-of-tarkov-concept/|title=Battlestate Games Shares EFT's \"Streets of Tarkov\" Environment Concept Art|date=2020-01-31|website=Future Game Releases|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref> The expected release date of Streets of Tarkov is April 20 2020. There would be a free-roam option in the game that would combine all the locations into one, giving an open-world experience for players in ''Escape of Tarkov''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.futuregamereleases.com/2017/10/escape-tarkov-include-open-world/|title=Escape From Tarkov to Include Open World|date=2017-10-17|website=Future Game Releases|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>\n\n=== Factions ===\nThere are two [[Private military company|PMC]] factions for players to choose in the game: United Security (USEC), a [[Western world|Western]]-based company hired by a corporation known as TerraGroup to cover up the company's illegal activities and BEAR, a company created by the [[Government of Russia|Russian government]] to investigate these activities.<ref name=\":7\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.gosunoob.com/guides/tarkov-bear-or-usec-2020-which-faction-to-choose-in-escape-from-tarkov/|title=Tarkov BEAR or USEC 2020 - Which Faction to Choose in Escape From Tarkov|last=Ketchua|date=2020-02-12|website=GosuNoob.com Video Game News & Guides|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.chartattack.com/how-to-play-escape-from-tarkov-with-your-friends/|title=How to Play Escape from Tarkov with Your Friends 2020|last=Jonson|first=Jerrard|date=2020-03-13|website=Chart Attack|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref> It is planned that each faction would have its own gameplay advantages as well as unique cosmetics. For example, USEC-based players would specialize in Western or [[NATO]]-based firearms and light armor while BEAR-players would specialize in Russian firearms and heavy armor.<ref name=\":7\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://screenrant.com/escape-from-tarkov-bear-usec-faction-differences/|title=Escape From Tarkov: BEAR & USEC Differences|date=2020-02-07|website=ScreenRant|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref> \n\nAnother faction that is also playable as well as functioning as a NPC faction is the Scavs, which are aggressive locals of Tarkov that are hostile to both BEAR and USEC.<ref name=\":0\" /> There are Scav Raiders and Scav Bosses, which are both NPCs that have better equipment than normal Scavs, with the latter having a different [[artificial intelligence]] behavior and each specializing in a specific location in Tarkov.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailyesports.gg/escape-from-tarkov-scav-boss-guide-where-to-find-and-eliminate-them/|title=Escape from Tarkov Scav Boss guide: Where to find and eliminate them|date=2020-01-17|website=Daily Esports|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.invenglobal.com/articles/10090/escape-from-tarkov-everything-you-need-to-know-about-the-hottest-game-on-twitch|title=Escape from Tarkov: Everything you need to know about the hottest game on Twitch|website=www.invenglobal.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>\n\n== Development ==\n{{Expand section|date=March 2020}}\n''Escape from Tarkov'' began development in 2012.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vg247.com/2016/02/25/the-level-of-detail-in-escape-from-tarkov-is-rather-impressive-already/|title=The level of detail in Escape From Tarkov is rather impressive already|date=2016-02-25|website=VG247|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref> Battlestate Games lead developer Nikita Buyanov stated that he and the staff gained their experience through working at Absolutsoft on their previous work ''Contract Wars''.<ref name=\":0\" /> Both ''Escape from Tarkov'' and ''Contract Wars'' are set in what the developers refer to as the Russia-2028 universe.<ref name=\":8\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/2016/6/3/11841338/escape-from-tarkov-has-us-excited-about-the-hardcore-survival-genre-again|title=Escape From Tarkov has us excited about the hardcore survival genre again|last=Hall|first=Charlie|date=2016-06-03|website=Polygon|language=en|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref> Buyanov stated that some of his staff also had experience from real-world military experience, with one of them being a former [[Spetsnaz]] operator.<ref name=\":8\" />\n\n== Release ==\nDevelopers stated that ''Escape from Tarkov'' would be a traditional full purchase [[Software release life cycle|release]] without any [[free-to-play]] or [[microtransaction]] elements. There is a possibility of a release on [[Steam (software)|Steam]] sometime after the game's official release. There are also plans for [[downloadable content]] in the future.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/how-modding-microtransactions-and-death-will-work-/1100-6436115/|title=How Modding, Microtransactions, and Death Will Work in Escape from Tarkov|newspaper=GameSpot|access-date=2017-02-18|language=en}}</ref> The early-access version of the game is released in four editions, with the latter having more equipment and a larger stash for the player to use than the former: Standard Edition, Left Behind Edition, Prepare For Escape Edition, and Edge of Darkness Limited Edition.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/escape-from-tarkov-pre-orders-all-early-access-edi/1100-6472569/|title=Escape From Tarkov Pre-Orders: All Early Access Editions Compared|website=GameSpot|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref> \n\n''Escape from Tarkov'' was launched as a closed [[Video game development#Alpha|alpha]] game that was first made available to select users on 4 August 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pcgamesn.com/escape-from-tarkov/alpha-date-revealed|title=Check your inbox: Escape from Tarkov\u2019s closed alpha kicks off on August 4|website=PCGamesN|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref> Battlestate Games then announced that the game would go into its extended alpha stage on 28 December 2016, which would available to select users who [[Preorder|preordered]] the game.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.pcgamesn.com/escape-from-tarkov/escape-from-tarkov-extended-alpha|title=FPS/MMO Escape from Tarkov gets new raid location and weapon failure in extended alpha|newspaper=PCGamesN|access-date=2017-02-18}}</ref> This is the stage where Battlestate released the game in four preorder tiers, with the Edge of Darkness edition guaranteeing players access to the alpha build.<ref name=\":1\" /> All players who had access were subject to a [[non-disclosure agreement]] (NDA) and video coverage of the [[gameplay]] via [[Video game live streaming|streaming]] was limited to a few select players until 24 March 2017, when the NDA was lifted.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamingcypher.com/escape-tarkov-nda-now-lifted/|title=Escape From Tarkov NDA Now Lifted|date=2017-03-24|website=Gaming Cypher|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>\n\nThe game entered closed [[Video game development#Beta|beta]] on 28 July 2017, being made available to all players no matter what pre-order edition was bought.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pcgamer.com/escape-from-tarkovs-closed-beta-available-now-to-those-who-preorder/|title=Escape From Tarkov's closed beta available now to those who preorder|last=Paget|first=Mat|date=2017-07-30|website=PC Gamer|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref> As of April 2020, ''Escape from Tarkov'' is still currently in its beta stage.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.escapefromtarkov.com/|title=Pre-order - Escape from Tarkov|website=www.escapesfromtarkov.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>\n\n== Controversy ==\nBattlestate Games has been accused of abusing YouTube's [[DMCA]] system to remove negative videos of Escape from Tarkov. YouTube user Eroktic released a video accusing Battlestate Games of leaking user information, resulting in Battlestate Games issuing DMCAs on 47 YouTube videos posted by the user; two of which were striked for allegedly spreading false information and the rest for spreading \"negative hype\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/2018/12/17/18145139/escape-from-tarkov-dmca-youtube-eroktic|title=Escape From Tarkov team barrages YouTuber with DMCA takedowns over 'misinformation'|last=Hall|first=Charlie|date=2018-12-17|accessdate=2018-12-19|work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.oneangrygamer.net/2018/12/escape-from-tarkov-devs-abuse-dmca-takedowns-against-eroktics-youtube-content/73733/|title=Escape From Tarkov Devs Abuse DMCA Takedowns Against Eroktic\u2019s YouTube Content|date=2018-12-18|accessdate=2018-12-19|work=One Angry Gamer}}</ref>\n\nIn a 2016 interview, an employee working for a game developer Pavel Dyatlov stated that there would be no women or playable female characters in the game because, \"... women can't handle that amount of stress. There's only place for hardened men in this place.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://wccftech.com/escape-tarkov-interview-truly-hardcore-first-person-shooter/|title=Escape from Tarkov Interview \u2013 A Truly Hardcore First Person Shooter Due in 2016|date=2016-09-06|accessdate=2020-01-16|work=Alessio Palumbo}}</ref>.\n\nLater in 2020, the developers apologized for the previously expressed views and instead stated the reason for not adding playable female characters is because of \"game lore and more importantly, the huge amount of work needed with animations, gear fitting etc.\"{{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n== External links ==\n*[https://escapefromtarkovsettings.com/ Escape From Tarkov Settings]\n[[Category:Upcoming video games]]\n[[Category:Video games set in Russia]]\n[[Category:Unity (game engine) games]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in Russia]]\n[[Category:Windows-only games]]\n[[Category:First-person shooter multiplayer online games]]\n[[Category:Tactical shooter video games]]\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|{{Tone|date=September 2019}}{{Lead too short|date=January 2020}}{{3p|date=March 2020}}}}\n{{Infobox video game\n| title = Escape from Tarkov\n| image = Escape from Tarkov.jpg\n| caption = Cover art for ''Escape from Tarkov''\n| developer = Battlestate Games\n| publisher = Battlestate Games\n| engine = [[Unity (game engine)|Unity]]\n| platforms = [[Microsoft Windows]]\n| genre = [[Action RPG]], [[Simulator]], [[First-person shooter]]\n| modes = [[Multi-player video game|Multi-player]], [[Arena-mode]], [[Nonlinear gameplay|Freeroam]]\n| released = Unreleased (Closed beta released on July 27th, 2017)\n| designer = \n| writer = \n| composer = \n| alt = \n}}\n\n'''''Escape from Tarkov''''' is an [[Indie game|indie]], [[Massively multiplayer online game|massively multiplayer online]] (MMO), [[first-person shooter]] (FPS) [[video game]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.escapefromtarkov.com/#about|title=About|website=www.escapesfromtarkov.com|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref> being developed by the Russian studio Battlestate Games to be released on [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]]. It is set in the fictional Norvinsk region in [[Northwest Russia|Northwestern Russia]], where a war is taking place between two [[Private military company|private military companies]] (United Security and BEAR) over a [[political scandal]] regarding the area's \"[[special economic zone]]\". The player is tasked with escaping the city of Tarkov by either joining one of the private military companies, or by trying to acquire precious loot from the sealed areas.\n\nA closed [[Video game development#Alpha|alpha]] of the game was first made available to select users on August 4, 2016,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.escapefromtarkov.com/news/id/28|title=Closed Alpha testing announce|website=www.escapesfromtarkov.com|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref> followed by a closed beta in July 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.escapefromtarkov.com/news/id/68|title=Closed Beta will start in July!|website=www.escapesfromtarkov.com|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref>\n\n== Gameplay ==\nThe developers of ''Escape from Tarkov'' refer the game as a realistic and hardcore [[first-person shooter]] [[Role-playing video game|role-playing]] video game that borrows elements from [[Massively multiplayer online game|massively multiplayer online games]].<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/escape-from-tarkov-pre-orders-all-early-access-edi/1100-6472569/|title=Escape From Tarkov Pre-Orders: All Early Access Editions Compared|website=GameSpot|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref><ref name=\":5\" /> In its current state, ''Escape from Tarkov'' incorporates several modes for the players to play: online [[Private military company|PMC]] raids, scav raids (short for \"scavenger\"),<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamespot.com/videos/what-is-the-new-scav-faction-in-escape-from-tarkov/2300-6437413/|title=What Is The New Scav Faction In Escape From Tarkov?|website=GameSpot|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pcgamesn.com/escape-from-tarkov/how-to-guide-tips|title=How to escape from Tarkov: our tips and guide|website=PCGamesN|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref><ref name=\":6\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/2020/1/21/21071120/escape-from-tarkov-guide-how-to-best-loot-scav-run-explained|title=Escape from Tarkov guide: How to get the best loot from a Scav run|last=Goslin|first=Austen|date=2020-01-21|website=Polygon|language=en|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref> and a temporary offline mode.<ref name=\":2\" /> In these raids, players can choose to play solo or go in groups and spawn on one side of a variety of maps to choose from in the game.<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.pcgamer.com/escape-from-tarkov-is-a-daunting-and-savage-evolution-of-battle-royale/|title=Escape From Tarkov is a daunting and savage evolution of battle royale|last=Messner|first=Steven|date=2020-01-18|website=PC Gamer|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref> Once spawned in, the players are given an extraction point on the other side of the map, and must fight against other players and scav [[Non-player character|non-player characters]] (NPC) to reach that point in order to escape.<ref name=\":4\" /> In addition to combat, players can also find loot in these maps such as firearms, equipment, armor, etc. and once extracted, can store their loot in a stash to use in future raids or can be sold in a flea market.<ref name=\":4\" />\n\nWhen players die in a raid, they lose everything, including loot and the equipment they brought into the raid.<ref name=\":4\" /> Players can insure weapons and equipment they brought in to increase the chances of retaining it if they are not already stolen by other players.<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.pcgamesn.com/escape-from-tarkov/how-to-guide-tips|title=How to escape from Tarkov: our tips and guide|website=PCGamesN|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref><ref name=\":4\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/pc-exclusive-shooter-escape-from-tarkov-closed-bet/1100-6451230/|title=PC-Exclusive Shooter Escape From Tarkov Closed Beta Date Announced|website=GameSpot|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref> As mentioned before, players can also play as a scav in a raid, where players are given a random loadout to use and do not lose anything from their stash when they die as a scav, making scav modes a learning source in the game.<ref name=\":3\" /><ref name=\":4\" /> If a player dies as a scav, there is a cooldown timer until the scav mode becomes available again for the player.<ref name=\":6\" />\n\nWhile not in a raid, players can sell their loot to traders that are provided by the game. These traders can provide a variety of quests that players can fulfill to increase their trader loyalty to get access to more items that can be purchased from the trader and more quests as well.<ref name=\":5\" /> Players can also settle and upgrade a living area called \"the Hideout,\" which is an underground bomb shelter that once upgraded with the materials needed, give the players in-game bonuses.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamepur.com/guides/escape-from-tarkov-hideout|title=What does the Escape from Tarkov Hideout do?|date=2020-01-17|website=Gamepur|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref> These bonuses include reducing the cooldown timer to play as a scav.<ref name=\":6\" />\n\n=== Combat ===\n{{Expand section|date=March 2020}}\n''Escape from Tarkov'' has combat that could be described as hardcore and realistic. The player has potential access to a variety of weapons ranging from AR's, SMG's, shotguns, sniper rifles, etc. All of these weapons, adjacent to other shooter games, are effective at various ranges dependent upon several variables like player position and distance from the enemy. Weapon effectiveness and functionality is heavily dependent upon the attachments and mods that the player installs on the weapon, such as sights and barrel attachments. The major difference between the combat in ''Escape from Tarkov'' and other FPS games is how damage is dealt. Instead of a standard health bar, players take damage to different areas and limbs of the body. Depending on the weapon type and the damage dealt, various status effects can be applied to a player's limbs that drastically effect how the PC moves and functions such as fractures and bleeding. Damage can be effectively avoided depending on player movement and gear. Body armor can protect certain areas of the body and leaning mechanics can allow a player to reduce their visible hit box to the enemy.\nObservers find ''Escape from Tarkov''<nowiki/>'s hardcore combat to be similar to that of [[Bohemia Interactive|Bohemia Interactive's]] [[ARMA (series)|''ARMA'']].<ref name=\":4\" />\n\n== Synopsis ==\n\n=== Setting ===\n''Escape from Tarkov'' is set in the fictional city of Tarkov, the capital of the Norvinsk [[Special economic zone|Special Economic Zone]] in [[Northwest Russia|Northwestern Russia]] between the year 2015 and 2026.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://unity.com/madewith/escape-from-tarkov|title=Escape from Tarkov by Battlestate Games - A shooter {{!}} Made with Unity|last=|first=|date=|website=Unity Technologies|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref> Political scandals and collapse of corruptions have resulted in the social breakdown of Tarkov and warring factions have turned the city into a shell of itself with sections of the city being under control of aggressive locals called \"scavs.\"<ref name=\":0\" /> As of March 2020, players can play across seven of the game's playable locations all within Tarkov: Factory, Customs, Woods, Shoreline, Interchange, The Lab, and Reserve.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dexerto.com/escape-from-tarkov/all-escape-from-tarkov-maps-and-extraction-points-guide-1309294|title=All Escape from Tarkov maps and extraction points guide|website=Dexerto.com|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref> Streets of Tarkov as of March 2020 is a location under development and is planned to become the next playable location in the game.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.futuregamereleases.com/2020/01/battlestate-games-shares-eft-streets-of-tarkov-concept/|title=Battlestate Games Shares EFT's \"Streets of Tarkov\" Environment Concept Art|date=2020-01-31|website=Future Game Releases|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref> The expected release date of Streets of Tarkov is April 20 2020. There would be a free-roam option in the game that would combine all the locations into one, giving an open-world experience for players in ''Escape of Tarkov''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.futuregamereleases.com/2017/10/escape-tarkov-include-open-world/|title=Escape From Tarkov to Include Open World|date=2017-10-17|website=Future Game Releases|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>\n\n=== Factions ===\nThere are two [[Private military company|PMC]] factions for players to choose in the game: United Security (USEC), a [[Western world|Western]]-based company hired by a corporation known as TerraGroup to cover up the company's illegal activities and BEAR, a company created by the [[Government of Russia|Russian government]] to investigate these activities.<ref name=\":7\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.gosunoob.com/guides/tarkov-bear-or-usec-2020-which-faction-to-choose-in-escape-from-tarkov/|title=Tarkov BEAR or USEC 2020 - Which Faction to Choose in Escape From Tarkov|last=Ketchua|date=2020-02-12|website=GosuNoob.com Video Game News & Guides|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.chartattack.com/how-to-play-escape-from-tarkov-with-your-friends/|title=How to Play Escape from Tarkov with Your Friends 2020|last=Jonson|first=Jerrard|date=2020-03-13|website=Chart Attack|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref> It is planned that each faction would have its own gameplay advantages as well as unique cosmetics. For example, USEC-based players would specialize in Western or [[NATO]]-based firearms and light armor while BEAR-players would specialize in Russian firearms and heavy armor.<ref name=\":7\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://screenrant.com/escape-from-tarkov-bear-usec-faction-differences/|title=Escape From Tarkov: BEAR & USEC Differences|date=2020-02-07|website=ScreenRant|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref> \n\nAnother faction that is also playable as well as functioning as a NPC faction is the Scavs, which are aggressive locals of Tarkov that are hostile to both BEAR and USEC.<ref name=\":0\" /> There are Scav Raiders and Scav Bosses, which are both NPCs that have better equipment than normal Scavs, with the latter having a different [[artificial intelligence]] behavior and each specializing in a specific location in Tarkov.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailyesports.gg/escape-from-tarkov-scav-boss-guide-where-to-find-and-eliminate-them/|title=Escape from Tarkov Scav Boss guide: Where to find and eliminate them|date=2020-01-17|website=Daily Esports|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.invenglobal.com/articles/10090/escape-from-tarkov-everything-you-need-to-know-about-the-hottest-game-on-twitch|title=Escape from Tarkov: Everything you need to know about the hottest game on Twitch|website=www.invenglobal.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>\n\n== Development ==\n{{Expand section|date=March 2020}}\n''Escape from Tarkov'' began development in 2012.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vg247.com/2016/02/25/the-level-of-detail-in-escape-from-tarkov-is-rather-impressive-already/|title=The level of detail in Escape From Tarkov is rather impressive already|date=2016-02-25|website=VG247|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref> Battlestate Games lead developer Nikita Buyanov stated that he and the staff gained their experience through working at Absolutsoft on their previous work ''Contract Wars''.<ref name=\":0\" /> Both ''Escape from Tarkov'' and ''Contract Wars'' are set in what the developers refer to as the Russia-2028 universe.<ref name=\":8\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/2016/6/3/11841338/escape-from-tarkov-has-us-excited-about-the-hardcore-survival-genre-again|title=Escape From Tarkov has us excited about the hardcore survival genre again|last=Hall|first=Charlie|date=2016-06-03|website=Polygon|language=en|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref> Buyanov stated that some of his staff also had experience from real-world military experience, with one of them being a former [[Spetsnaz]] operator.<ref name=\":8\" />\n\n== Release ==\nDevelopers stated that ''Escape from Tarkov'' would be a traditional full purchase [[Software release life cycle|release]] without any [[free-to-play]] or [[microtransaction]] elements. There is a possibility of a release on [[Steam (software)|Steam]] sometime after the game's official release. There are also plans for [[downloadable content]] in the future.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/how-modding-microtransactions-and-death-will-work-/1100-6436115/|title=How Modding, Microtransactions, and Death Will Work in Escape from Tarkov|newspaper=GameSpot|access-date=2017-02-18|language=en}}</ref> The early-access version of the game is released in four editions, with the latter having more equipment and a larger stash for the player to use than the former: Standard Edition, Left Behind Edition, Prepare For Escape Edition, and Edge of Darkness Limited Edition.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/escape-from-tarkov-pre-orders-all-early-access-edi/1100-6472569/|title=Escape From Tarkov Pre-Orders: All Early Access Editions Compared|website=GameSpot|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref> \n\n''Escape from Tarkov'' was launched as a closed [[Video game development#Alpha|alpha]] game that was first made available to select users on 4 August 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pcgamesn.com/escape-from-tarkov/alpha-date-revealed|title=Check your inbox: Escape from Tarkov\u2019s closed alpha kicks off on August 4|website=PCGamesN|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref> Battlestate Games then announced that the game would go into its extended alpha stage on 28 December 2016, which would available to select users who [[Preorder|preordered]] the game.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.pcgamesn.com/escape-from-tarkov/escape-from-tarkov-extended-alpha|title=FPS/MMO Escape from Tarkov gets new raid location and weapon failure in extended alpha|newspaper=PCGamesN|access-date=2017-02-18}}</ref> This is the stage where Battlestate released the game in four preorder tiers, with the Edge of Darkness edition guaranteeing players access to the alpha build.<ref name=\":1\" /> All players who had access were subject to a [[non-disclosure agreement]] (NDA) and video coverage of the [[gameplay]] via [[Video game live streaming|streaming]] was limited to a few select players until 24 March 2017, when the NDA was lifted.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamingcypher.com/escape-tarkov-nda-now-lifted/|title=Escape From Tarkov NDA Now Lifted|date=2017-03-24|website=Gaming Cypher|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>\n\nThe game entered closed [[Video game development#Beta|beta]] on 28 July 2017, being made available to all players no matter what pre-order edition was bought.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pcgamer.com/escape-from-tarkovs-closed-beta-available-now-to-those-who-preorder/|title=Escape From Tarkov's closed beta available now to those who preorder|last=Paget|first=Mat|date=2017-07-30|website=PC Gamer|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref> As of April 2020, ''Escape from Tarkov'' is still currently in its beta stage.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.escapefromtarkov.com/|title=Pre-order - Escape from Tarkov|website=www.escapesfromtarkov.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>\n\n== Controversy ==\nBattlestate Games has been accused of abusing YouTube's [[DMCA]] system to remove negative videos of Escape from Tarkov. YouTube user Eroktic released a video accusing Battlestate Games of leaking user information, resulting in Battlestate Games issuing DMCAs on 47 YouTube videos posted by the user; two of which were striked for allegedly spreading false information and the rest for spreading \"negative hype\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/2018/12/17/18145139/escape-from-tarkov-dmca-youtube-eroktic|title=Escape From Tarkov team barrages YouTuber with DMCA takedowns over 'misinformation'|last=Hall|first=Charlie|date=2018-12-17|accessdate=2018-12-19|work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.oneangrygamer.net/2018/12/escape-from-tarkov-devs-abuse-dmca-takedowns-against-eroktics-youtube-content/73733/|title=Escape From Tarkov Devs Abuse DMCA Takedowns Against Eroktic\u2019s YouTube Content|date=2018-12-18|accessdate=2018-12-19|work=One Angry Gamer}}</ref>\n\nIn a 2016 interview, an employee working for a game developer Pavel Dyatlov stated that there would be no women or playable female characters in the game because, \"... women can't handle that amount of stress. There's only place for hardened men in this place.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://wccftech.com/escape-tarkov-interview-truly-hardcore-first-person-shooter/|title=Escape from Tarkov Interview \u2013 A Truly Hardcore First Person Shooter Due in 2016|date=2016-09-06|accessdate=2020-01-16|work=Alessio Palumbo}}</ref>.\n\nLater in 2020, the developers apologized for the previously expressed views and instead stated the reason for not adding playable female characters is because of \"game lore and more importantly, the huge amount of work needed with animations, gear fitting etc.\"{{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n== External links ==\n*[https://escapefromtarkovsettings.com/ Escape From Tarkov Settings]\n[[Category:Upcoming video games]]\n[[Category:Video games set in Russia]]\n[[Category:Unity (game engine) games]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in Russia]]\n[[Category:Windows-only games]]\n[[Category:First-person shooter multiplayer online games]]\n[[Category:Tactical shooter video games]]\n", "name_user": "Bdoghomieg123", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eGameplay:Minor Wording Change", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Escape_from_Tarkov"}
{"title_page": "Brian Flores", "text_new": "{{short description|American football coach}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox NFL biography\n| name                = Brian Flores\n| image               = \n| alt                 = \n| caption             = \n| current_team        = Miami Dolphins\n| position            = [[Head coach]]\n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|1981|2|24|mf=y}}\n| birth_place         = [[Brooklyn, New York]]\n| death_date          = \n| death_place         = \n| high_school         = [[Poly Prep Country Day School|Brooklyn (NY) Poly Prep]] \n| college             = [[Boston College]]\n| pastcoaching        = \n* [[New England Patriots]] ({{NFL year|2004}}\u2013{{NFL year|2018}})<br>- Scouting assistant (2004\u20132005) <br>- Pro scout (2006\u20132007) <br>- Special teams assistant (2008\u20132009) <br>- Assistant offense & special teams coach (2010) <br>- Defensive assistant (2011) <br>- Safeties coach (2012\u20132015) <br>- Linebackers coach (2016\u20132018)\n* [[Miami Dolphins]] (2019\u2013present)<br>Head coach\n| highlights          = \n* 4\u00d7 [[Super Bowl]] champion ([[Super Bowl XXXIX|XXXIX]], [[Super Bowl XLIX|XLIX]], [[Super Bowl LI|LI]], [[Super Bowl LIII|LIII]])\n| regular_record = {{Winning percentage|5|11|record=y}}\n| pfrcoach            = \n}}\n\n'''Brian Flores''' (born February 24, 1981) is an [[American football]] coach who is the [[head coach]] of the [[Miami Dolphins]] of the [[National Football League]] (NFL). Prior to joining the Dolphins, Flores served in multiple roles with the [[New England Patriots]] since their [[2004 New England Patriots season|2004 Super Bowl-winning season]]. During his tenure with the Patriots, the Patriots won four Super Bowls, fourteen AFC East titles, and seven [[AFC Championship]]s. He is also the second former [[Bill Belichick]] assistant to be named Dolphins head coach, the first being [[Nick Saban]].\n\n==Early life==\nFlores was born and raised in [[Brownsville, Brooklyn|Brownsville]] in [[Brooklyn, New York]] to [[Hondurans|Honduran]] parents. <ref name=\"ESPN_profile\">{{cite news | url=http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/22262842/brian-flores-new-england-patriots-next-coaching-star-emerge-bill-belichick-tree | title= The Patriots' next coaching star? His odds were incredibly long | author=Ian O'Connor | date=January 30, 2017 | work=ESPN.com}}</ref> After attending [[Poly Prep Country Day School]] in Brooklyn, Flores played football at [[Boston College]] as a linebacker from 1999 through 2003. An injury prevented him from playing in the NFL.<ref name=\"ESPN_profile\" />\n\n==Coaching career==\n===New England Patriots===\nIn [[2004 New England Patriots season|2004]], Flores joined the Patriots as a scouting assistant, the same year they would win their 3rd Super Bowl title in [[Super Bowl XXXIX]]. He became a pro scout in [[2006 New England Patriots season|2006]] before moving to the coaching staff as a special teams coaching assistant in [[2008 New England Patriots season|2008]]. His title was changed to assistant coach offense/special teams in [[2010 New England Patriots season|2010]]. He was named defensive assistant in [[2011 New England Patriots season|2011]]. In [[2012 New England Patriots season|2012]], he was named safeties' coach.  He was named linebackers' coach ahead of the [[2016 New England Patriots season|2016]] season. In 2018, he took over the Patriots' defensive playcalling duties after the departure of [[defensive coordinator]] [[Matt Patricia]], but was not given the title of defensive coordinator.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/22677963/brian-flores-lead-new-england-patriots-defense-title|title=Brian Flores to call Pats' defensive plays without DC title|date=March 7, 2018|publisher=espn.com|accessdate=March 20, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Miami Dolphins===\nOn February 4, 2019, Flores was hired as head coach of the [[Miami Dolphins]], becoming the fourth Latino in NFL history to become a head coach, after [[Ron Rivera]], [[Tom Fears]], and [[Tom Flores]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/25925144/dolphins-make-patriots-assistant-brian-flores-coach|title=Dolphins make Patriots assistant Brian Flores their next head coach|first=Cameron|last=Wolfe|date=February 4, 2019|work=ESPN}}</ref> On September 8, 2019, the Dolphins lost to the [[Baltimore Ravens]] 59-10 in Flores' head coaching debut. Again in week two, the Dolphins lost 43-0 to Flores' former team, the [[New England Patriots]], leaving the Dolphins outscored by 92 points within the first two weeks of the season. On November 3, 2019, Flores recorded his first win as a head coach in a 26-18 home victory over the division rival [[2019 New York Jets season|New York Jets]], led by Flores' predecessor and former Dolphins head coach [[Adam Gase]]. He followed this by earning his second consecutive win against the [[Indianapolis Colts]] the following week, which was Miami's first road win since Week 2 of the [[2018 Miami Dolphins season|2018 season]]. Flores' first season as head coach concluded with a 27-24 upset win over his former team, the [[New England Patriots]], and was also the Dolphins' first road win over the Pats since [[2008 Miami Dolphins season|2008]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Sullivan |first1=Tyler |title=Patriots vs. Dolphins final score: Miami pulls off stunner, sends New England down to No. 3 playoff seed |url=https://www.cbssports.com/nfl/news/patriots-vs-dolphins-final-score-miami-pulls-off-stunner-sends-new-england-down-to-the-no-3-seed/live/ |website=CBS Sports}}</ref> The Dolphins finished the season 5-11.\n\n==Head coaching record==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 95%; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"|Team !! rowspan=\"2\"|Year !! colspan=\"5\"|Regular season !! colspan=\"4\"|Postseason\n|-\n! Won !! Lost !! Ties !! Win % !! Finish !! Won !! Lost !! Win % !! Result\n|-\n! [[2019 Miami Dolphins season|MIA]] || [[2019 NFL season|2019]]\n| 5 || 11